Function Documentation

const char* getImage (  ImageCode  imageCode,
ImageSet  imageSet = DEFAULT
) 
 

Gets the image name for an image.

If there is no specific name for the image, we will try the DEFAULT imageSet.

Parameters:
imageCode The image.
imageSet The image set.
Returns:
The image name as a string, add extension to get a filename.

ImageSet getImageSetFromString (  const MC2String &  imageSetStr  ) 
 

Converts a string representation of an image set to an ImageTable::ImageSet.

The string representation is used in navclientsettings.

Parameters:
imageSetStr The string representation, e.g. "iphone".
Returns:
The image set, e.g. DEFAULT.

MC2String imageSetToString (  ImageSet  imageSet  ) 
 

Converts an ImageTable::ImageSet to a string representation which can be used for debugging/logging purposes.

Parameters:
imageSet The image set to convert.
Returns:
The string representation.
